docs.abstract: Foreign investors betting on artificial intelligence are pouring money into the company’s shares. Analysts say it will have a hard time keeping up with rivals.
docs.snippet: Foreign investors betting on artificial intelligence are pouring money into the company’s shares. Analysts say it will have a hard time keeping up with rivals.
docs.lead_paragraph: The introduction of ChatGPT has lit a fire under the shares of companies that produce microchips, the brains of artificial intelligence. Bets on the potential of so-called generative A.I. have poured in. The most eye-catching example of the rally is Silicon Valley’s Nvidia, the top seller of chips used in artificial intelligence, whose shares are up nearly 200 percent this year.

headline.main: Samsung’s A.I. Moment Is Here, but Is It Ready?
headline.print_headline: Foreign Investors Pour Money Into Samsung’s A.I. Venture, But It Faces Stiff Competition
